<h2>How to Set Up and Use the Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask</h2>
<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.25rem;margin:1.25rem 0;">
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Charge and pair</strong><p>Fully charge the mask via USB-C (about 2 hours). On your phone, enable Bluetooth, then hold the mask's power button for 3 seconds until the LED flashes. Select "Boodlab" in your phone's Bluetooth settings and confirm pairing. It will auto-reconnect after the first time.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Adjust and wear</strong><p>Slide the rear strap adjuster so the mask sits snug across your face for full light blockout. Make sure there's no pressure on your ears or temples. The 3D contoured eye cups should feel lifted and comfortable, not pressing against your eyelids.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Play and sleep</strong><p>Start your podcast, audiobook, or white noise on your phone. Use the onboard +/- buttons on the mask to adjust volume and the play/pause button to control playback without touching your phone. Set a sleep timer and drift off.</p></div></div>
