<!-- §15 FAQ -->
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq supporting-questions">
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Does the Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask work for side sleepers?</h3><p>Yes â it's specifically designed for side sleepers. The speakers are ultra-flat and flush with the mask surface, so there's no hard plastic pressing against your ear when you roll over. The 3D eye cups also lift away from your eyelids, keeping the blackout seal intact even when you're on your side.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does the battery last on the Boodlab sleep mask?</h3><p>Battery life is 8â10 hours on a full charge at moderate volume, which covers a full night's sleep. Charging takes roughly 2 hours via USB. If you use it at higher volumes or pair via a phone that streams lossless audio, expect the lower end of that range.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can you use the Boodlab sleep mask without Bluetooth â just as a blackout mask?</h3><p>Yes. You don't need to power it on to use it as a blackout mask. The 3D contoured foam blocks light effectively on its own. Just wear it unpowered if you only want darkness, no audio.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is the Boodlab sleep mask machine washable?</h3><p>The fabric shell is removable and hand-washable. Remove the speaker unit before washing. Do not machine wash or submerge the electronics. Air dry completely before reassembling.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How does the Boodlab Bluetooth Sleep Mask compare to a regular sleep mask with speakers?</h3><p>Boodlab is specifically engineered for comfort during sleep with flat embedded speakers, 3D eye cups, and side-sleeper optimization. Regular sleep masks with speakers often have bulkier, protruding hardware that creates pressure points and discomfort. Boodlab prioritizes zero-pressure contact on the face.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I adjust the speaker volume with physical controls, or only via the phone app?</h3><p>The Boodlab mask has built-in volume and playback controls integrated into the headband itself. You can adjust volume, play/pause, and skip tracks without touching your phone. This is ideal for adjusting in the dark without waking fully.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is the mask suitable for people with sensitive skin?</h3><p>The padding uses hypoallergenic, soft foam that's gentle on sensitive skin. However, if you have severe dermatitis or latex allergies, check the material specs first. Most sensitive-skin users report good tolerance, but extended wear may cause minor marks from the headband.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How does the adjustable strap fit different head sizes?</h3><p>The elastic headband stretches to accommodate head sizes from small to extra-large. The strap adjusts in both width and length for a personalized fit. Most users find it fits comfortably within 2-3 nights of adjustment.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I use the Boodlab mask for meditation or relaxation, not just sleep?</h3><p>Yes. Many users wear it during meditation, yoga, naps, or relaxation sessions. The full blackout combined with audio makes it perfect for guided meditations or ambient music during downtime. It's not limited to nighttime sleep.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>What audio codec does the Bluetooth connection support?</h3><p>The mask supports standard Bluetooth audio codecs (SBC, A2DP). It doesn't support premium codecs like aptX or LDAC, but sound quality is optimized for sleep content (white noise, ambient, podcasts) rather than high-fidelity music. Latency is low enough for apps and meditation.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is this mask suitable for hot sleepers, or does the electronics trap heat?</h3><p>The Boodlab mask is designed with breathable padding and doesn't trap significant heat. However, the headband and electronics do add some warmth compared to a passive blackout mask. Hot sleepers should test it or look for a passive-only blackout mask if thermal comfort is critical.</p></div>
</div>

